body: Diamanda Galas – Let My People Go This song both terrifies me and excites me! Galas has vocal and piano skills like no other. No one has interpreted the blues like this and no one ever will!            Sinéad O’Connor – Troy So vulnerable and emotional, so real and raw. Like most O’Connor classics, it works without a real chorus and has a tense build up instead.             PJ Harvey – 50 Foot Queenie (4-track demo version) This track makes me feel powerful and like I have a huge … guitar between my legs.       Nicki Minaj – Did It on Em Nicki Minaj rules over all other rappers! This song is so silly and brilliant. I love it and I wish I wrote this masterpiece.            Paula Temple – Gegen  She is the best techno producer in the game right now! Paula Temple also remixed the song Rub for my upcoming remix album Rub Remixed.             Cyndi Lauper – When You Were Mine Prince’s great lyrics and Cyndi’s insane vocals. It’s tough to outdo Prince on his own song, but here, Cyndi Lauper’s emotion is incredibly raw and unmatched.             Peaches’ new album Rub Remixed is out 3 June via Kartel Music Group
